% backtrace_sourceloc.trx
% Demonstrates Type::SourceLoc call-site locations in the backtrace.
%
% 'outer' is called directly from the stream on line 11 — that call is
% a direct stream execution so m_last_scan_location is exact.  'inner'
% is called from inside outer's proc body, so its SourceLoc records the
% current stream position (outer's call site) rather than the exact
% position of 'inner' inside the proc definition; this is the known
% approximation for proc-body calls.

/inner { 1 0 div } def
/outer { inner } def
outer
